  "prompt": "Are there any hotels in Goa which could be safe for unmarried couples?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several hotels in Goa that are known to be friendly and safe for unmarried couples. Many accommodations such as beach resorts, boutique hotels, and guesthouses cater to both families and couples, and they generally do not have strict policies against unmarried couples.\n\nHere are a few tips for finding a suitable hotel:\n\n1. **Check Reviews**: Look for hotels that have good reviews from couples, particularly those mentioning a friendly environment for unmarried guests.\n\n2. **Book Online**: Websites like MakeMyTrip, Booking.com, and Airbnb allow you to filter accommodations and check the policies regarding couples.\n\n3. **Choose Popular Areas**: Areas like South Goa (Palolem, Agonda) and North Goa (Anjuna, Baga) have several hotels that are accustomed to hosting young travelers and couples.\n\n4. **Contact Hotels Directly**: If you're unsure about a particular hotel, it\u2019s a good idea to call ahead and inquire about their policies regarding unmarried couples.\n\n5. **Consider Local Regulations**: Although Goa is generally more liberal than other parts of India, it's still good to be cautious and ensure that the hotel respects your privacy and comfort.\n\nSome well-rated hotels known for being couple-friendly include:\n\n- **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa** (Benaulim)\n- **W Goa** (Vagator)\n- **Alila Diwa Goa** (Majorda)\n- **Radisson Blu Resort Goa** (Cavelossim)\n- **Cabo de Rama Resort** (Cabo de Rama)\n\nAlways ensure to check the latest reviews and their policies before booking, as circumstances can change.",
